Description: Fragment of handle-plate of a pottery column-krater; underside and edges glazed; on top, two rays flanked by volutes. Fine buff-brown clay with small mica inclusions. Incised inscription.
Bibliographic references: Petrie 1886 / Naukratis. Part I., 1884-85 (pl. XXXIV, no. 435)
Bernand 1970 / Le Delta égyptien d'après les textes grecs, i: les confins libyques (p. 673, no. 317)
Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GG.1225)
